<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-11-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-11-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="735" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d735">
                            <head>No. 732.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hall</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telgram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Havana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-11-18"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 18,
                                        1873</date>. (Received Nov. 18—10.10
                                p.m.)</dateline></opener>
                            <p>The consul at Santiago de Cuba reports, under date 13th instant? that
                                the total number of executions of persons from the Virginius was <pb facs="1174" n="1078" xml:id="pg_1078"/> fifty-three, and that
                                there had been no executions since 8th instant Statements published
                                here on 14th instant respecting fifty-seven additional executions
                                prove untrue. The British steamer Niobe was at Santiago, and the
                                Wyoming expected there on the 14th. The Virginius arrived here
                                to-day.</p>
                            <closer><signed>HALL.</signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>